The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Man killed in highway crash
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Man killed in highway crash
          A STAFF REPORTER                          The smashed car in which the Chatterjees were travelling. Picture by Gopal Senapati                                  
	A 40-year-old executive died and his wife and son were injured on Sunday morning when their WagonR slammed into the back of a mini-truck that had stopped suddenly on National Highway 6 because of a flat tyre.         
	Bhaskar Chatterjee, the head of the IT department of a private television channel, was at the wheel of the car when the mishap occurred at New Corola, under Domjur police station area, around 10am. He was pronounced dead at Howrah District Hospital        
	Bhaskars wife Sanghamitra, 36, and son Debroop, 6, were admitted to the hospital with head injuries. Their condition is stable, said doctors on Sunday evening.         
	The residents of Mandirtala in Shibpur were on their way to Sanghamitras parents house in Bagnan.        
	Both the mini-truck and the car were moving in the same direction at high speed. The car could not stop when the mini-truck suddenly halted because of the puncture, said an officer of Domjur police station.        
	The driver was slumped over the steering column and bleeding profusely from his wounds. The woman and the child were also bleeding. We took them to hospital, said a witness.        
	Bhaskars father Mani struggled to cope with the news in the familys two-storeyed home in Kashi Nath Chatterjee Lane.        
	Before leaving for his in-laws my son told me that he would be back by evening. We cannot believe that he would never return, said Mani.                                                                                                                                                           
